{
	"VersionNumber": 1,
	"ResourceName": "fortinet_log_ids",
	"Description": "This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Fortinet log types and subtypes. It is used within the Fortinet Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.\n\nfields:\ncategory,category_id,subcategory,subcategory_id,name,description,risk_score\n  - category: this is the log category for the event\n  - category_id: this is the log category id for the event\n  - subcategory: this is the log subcategory for the event\n  - subcategory_id: this is the log subcategory id for the event\n  - name: this is the log subcategory name for the event\n  - description: this is more information about the subcategory for the event\n  - risk_score: this is the associated risk score for the log category and subcategory\n\nReference(s):\n  - Fortinet \n    - https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/034314/log-id-numbers\n    - https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/656858/log-id-definitions\n    - https://docs.fortinet.com/document/fortigate/7.6.5/fortios-log-message-reference/160372\n\nUsage: lookup -r fortinet_log_ids subtype subcategory (category category_id subcategory subcategory_id name description risk_score)",
	"Labels": [
		"fortinet"
	],
